The Department states expenditures associated with the bill include an estimated $150,000
Turnpike System back-office software change order to accommodate the toll rate changes (based
on prior change orders completed with its vendor). The Department also states the bill would
require the issuance of free transponders for a 210-day period to New Hampshire residents who
open or currently maintain a New Hampshire E-ZPass account. Based on projected customer
activity and 10 percent growth, the Department estimates approximately 136,000 transponders
would be issued at a cost of $0.61 per transponder, for an estimated total cost of approximately
$82,960.
